<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,319,1137]" pageId="1" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1075,1100]" pageId="1" pageNumber="65">Comment.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[335,472,1077,1100]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Hyperstoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[335,472,1077,1100]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="65">Hyperstoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to the genera 
<taxonomicName authority="Maulik, 1921" authorityName="Maulik" authorityYear="1921" box="[858,1186,1076,1100]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lamellipalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[858,1018,1076,1100]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="65">Lamellipalpus</emphasis>
Maulik, 
<number box="[1130,1186,1076,1100]" pageId="1" pageNumber="65" value="1921.0">1921</number>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Maulik, 1921" authorityName="Maulik" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lamellipalpodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1249,1436,1076,1100]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="65">Lamellipalpodes</emphasis>
Maulik, 
<number box="[246,305,1112,1136]" pageId="1" pageNumber="65" value="1921.0">1921</number>
</taxonomicName>
. All the genera share a unique synapomorphic character: fused terminal and penultimate terga.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
